reviews.text: Authentic Hong Kong Cafe. No fancies, just real. Very good.

Delicious-but-inexpensive local fare in a typical Hong Kong greasy spoon. The place doesn't look like much, but the food is definitely above average. Not the cleanest place around, and the staff can be surly and sometimes a bit careless, but you don't go to this place for the decor or service quality.
Well priced tea set with average quality
Tea set start from 2:30pm which is a pretty good deal!
Food is great and flavorful and the servings are huge. Good enough for sharing. Value for money.
